713987f-a.title: Manhattan: 58th Street - 10th Avenue
713987f-a.text:
58th Street, north side, west from between Tenth and Eleventh
Avenues, showing at right tanks of the Amsterdam Gas Company,
and in the left centre background the Interborough Rapid
Transit Company power house.
May 20, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

710578f-a.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 58th Street
710578f-a.text:
Tenth Ave., west side, north from West 58th to 59th Streets, showing
oocupying this block front, the Haaren High School. This structure
formerly housed De Witt Clinton High School. View No. 2 depicts the
southern side of same, being the West 58th Street frontage as seen across
a clearance at the S.W. corner of this point.
December 19, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

Tenth Ave., west side, north from West 58th to 59th Streets, showing

710579f-a.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 58th Street
710579f-a.text:
Tenth Ave., east side, north from West 58th (right) Street. When
north of the next intersection this thoroughfare changes its namw to
become Amsterdam Ave. The low buildings on the right are units of Roose-
velt Hospital which occupies that entire block between 58th and 59th
Streets, east from Tenth to Ninth Aves. Occupying the westerly portion
of the next block are units of the College of Physicians and Surgeons
with the Sloane Maternity Hospital (7-story structure) at the N.E.
corner of 59th Street and the Vanderbilt Clinic (3-story) at the S.E.
corner of 60th Street.
November 30, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

710577f-a.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 58th Street
710577f-a.text:
Tenth Ave. (left), at and adjoining the S.W. corner of West 58th
(right) Street, showing a clearance at the corner where former Nos.
885 to 889 Amsterdam Ave. stood. Shown on the right is an extensive
view westward on West 58th Street, to the North (Hudson) River.
December 19, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
